{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01TFGnzrMQgRymU7ubfPyUx8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Full membership restored and the cluster is healthy.\n\n**Root cause:** The `es-config` ConfigMap had been corrupted in two ways:\n- `node.name:` was empty — the `${POD_NAME}` placeholder had been shell-expanded to nothing rather than left literal for Elasticsearch to substitute from the `POD_NAME` env var.\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed at the wrong namespace (`...es-cluster.default.svc.cluster.local` instead of the headless service in `elasticsearch`).\n\nes-cluster-0/1 kept running on their already-loaded config, but when es-cluster-2 restarted it loaded the broken config and crash-looped on `null-valued setting [node.name]`, dropping the cluster to 2 nodes.\n\n**Fix:** Restored the correct ConfigMap (literal `${POD_NAME}`, in-namespace seed hosts `es-cluster-N.es-cluster`) and restarted only es-cluster-2 so it picked up the corrected config. The two healthy nodes were never disrupted.\n\n**Verification:**\n1. Cluster health: **green**, 3 nodes.\n2. `/_cat/nodes` lists all three (es-cluster-0, -1, -2).\n3. `app-data` is readable (`count: 1`, all shards successful)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":667,"cache_read_input_tokens":41972,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":667},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4128a190-bfc4-435f-a8b7-4336acb428e8","uuid":"eb207931-2e2e-4085-90cd-a129316ccf44","request_id":"req_011CcAsmSMXjCgdVJEgmn9Nc"}
